### Examples of Formative Evaluation (Exam-Ready)

These are the examples UGC NET options will use. Memorise the category each falls under.

| Example | Why it is Formative |
|---|---|
| Class quiz after a chapter | Quick check of understanding mid-course |
| Teacher asking oral questions in class | Instant feedback during teaching |
| Assignment submission | Checks progress; teacher gives comments |
| Group discussion / seminar | Observes participation and understanding |
| Unit test (not final exam) | Tests a portion of syllabus during the course |
| Homework correction with feedback | Identifies errors while learning is ongoing |
| Student self-assessment checklist | Learner reflects on their own progress |
| Peer review of written work | Students give each other constructive feedback |
| Exit ticket (quick note at end of class) | Teacher sees what was understood that day |
| Observation of lab work | Assesses skills during practice, not after |

